 - You should be able to use aliases within aliases. For example:

     alias $tp /tmp/that/directory
     alias $new $tp/new

 - You should be able to replace the hostname functionality as well.

     set hostname on

   which prefixes the output with hostname:

 - When there are multiple definitions of the same alias, check which ones
   point to an existing directory. If multiple do, use the last one.
